Google Chrome remains the most popular Internet browser, according to data from NetMarketShare for January 2018. Chrome dominates the mobile and desktop market, with over 60% market share across desktop platforms and 59% market share on mobile. Safari is the main competitor to Chrome across mobile devices, with other mobile browsers trailing far behind. Internet Explorer beats Firefox for second place on desktop, and Microsoft Edge and Safari occupy the fourth and fifth spots respectively. The most popular Internet browsers across mobile and desktop for January 2018 are listed below.  